          <table width="580" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" align="center" style="border-top: 10px solid #005EA5;">
            <tbody><tr>
              <td width="100%" style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><h1 class="email" style="font-weight: 700; font-size: 48px; line-height: 1.041666667; margin: 30px 0;">Request  to close {!Transaction__c.CompanyName__c}</h1></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td width="100%" style="font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;">
                <p style="font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.315789474; margin: 0 0 30px 0;">
                The request to close has been <b>approved and signed</b> by all of the required directors/members. 
        
                <h2 style="font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.315789474; margin: 0 0 30px 0;">What happens next</h2>

                <p style="font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.315789474; margin: 0 0 30px 0;">
                Now that the request has been signed by all of the directors/members, it will need to be submitted within 90 days by the person filing the request to close. Once submitted we will notify the person submitting the request if the request to close has been accepted or rejected. </p>

                <p style="font-size: 19px; line-height: 1.315789474; margin: 0 0 30px 0;">
                It is the responsibility of directors to ensure that copies of the request are sent to all interested parties. This can include members (usually shareholders), creditors and employees, who must be notified within 7 days of submitting the completed request. The full list of who to tell can be found in the <a href='https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/company-strike-off-dissolution-and-restoration'>online guide.</a> </p>
                

              </td>
            </tr>
          </tbody></table>
        </td>
      </tr>
